<h2>Resin Comfort Flooring</h2>
<p>Comfort flooring is a seamless, polyurethane resin, that is designed to provide an aesthetic finish whilst soft underfoot. It challenges traditional soft flooring finishes such as lino and vinyl, as offers a similar look and feel, but is much more robust, seamless, easy to clean and can be completely bespoke. These qualities make comfort floor suitable for spaces like bedrooms, children’s rooms, rest areas for customers or a professional registered office.</p>
<p>Did you now that we can match any RAL colour to match your corporate branding, or favourite colour? We can also insert corporate logos into the floor to take your brand to the next level.</p>
<h2>How much does Resin Comfort Flooring Cost?</h2>
<p>The average resin floor cost per square meter is between £7 and £15 per meter squared for floor coating. If you want the ultimate resin flooring and opt for a high-performance polyurethane flooring, the resin floor cost per square meter jumps to between £50 &#8211; £100 per meter square.</p>
<h2>Liquid Vinyl Flooring</h2>
<p>Our liquid vinyl flooring is the ideal flooring option for office spaces in Belmont, with a seamless, decorative finish and multiple colours to choose from, this future proof flooring system is the perfect alternative to traditional vinyl and linoleum finishes.</p>
<ul>
<li>Seamless … no joints or weak points like vinyl.</li>
<li>Water resistant</li>
<li>Hygienic</li>
<li>Any RAL colour can be made or logo’s inserted</li>
<li>Robust</li>
<li>BREEAM A+ accredited … a sustainable flooring option</li>
<li>Easy to repair … no patches like vinyl</li>
</ul>
<h2>Wood Based Floor Coverings</h2>
<p>Wood based floor coverings help us create a cosy ambience while keeping the attractive wood effect. This comfort flooring is also good as a heat-insulating measure, making it a great installation option for a colder space.</p>
<p>Wood based floor coverings are not as durable as stone or concrete floors, but they can be much easier to install. This makes them ideal for a project that involves an indoor commercial or residential space rather than an industrial one.</p>
<h2>Cork Flooring Properties</h2>
<p>Just like cork flooring finishes, Comfort floors are durable and can match a diverse range of decorative finishes. Cork is often installed beneath vinyl finished to offer a solution which is softer under foot. This is not needed with comfort floor systems, as the polyurethane technology offers a soft and flexible, yet robust finish.</p>
<p>If you would like to receive even more information on Comfort Flooring options, make sure you get in touch with us today!</p>
<div class="blk-cta"><a class="blk-cta__lnk blue " href="#contact">Contact Our Team For Best Rates</a></div>
<h2>Hospital Flooring</h2>
<p>Comfort flooring is a fantastic option for hospitals, doctors’ surgery’s and healthcare facilities. Comfort floor is a seamless finish, which has no joints like traditional flooring types such as vinyl, meaning that bacteria ca not harbour in these weak points. Comfort floor also contains an anti-bacterial seal coat, which naturally eliminates bacteria growth. Another key advantage for hospitals is the acoustic values that the system offers, reducing noise between the floors of buildings, and also whilst walking around wards during night shifts.</p>
<p>Comfort floor also offers a high chemical resistance when compared to traditional flooring types, which is essential in a healthcare setting, whilst its easy to clean nature ensures spillages such as blood are easy to remove and dirt and bacteria does not harbour.</p>
<h2>Educational Resin Flooring (School, College, University)</h2>
<p>Comfort floor is the perfect solution for the education sector. Widley used in schools, colleges and universities, Comfort Floor offers an imaginative and creative floor finish, which can manipulate colour and design to make educational facilities really come to life.</p>
<p>Perfect for class rooms, dining rooms, social space and kitchens, comfort floors offer schools, colleges and universities a seamless, robust floor, which also has fantastic acoustic properties.</p>
<h2>Slip-Resistant Comfort Flooring</h2>
<p>Slip-resistance is important for all domestic and commercial flooring projects, and resin flooring is fantastic way to overcome any potential slip hazards. Comfort floors offer and anti-slip flooring profile, by adding a specified amount of glass bead into the seal coat. This means that comfort floors hits all of the health and safety requirements from the HSE, and can be demonstrated to record values above 36 pvt on the pendulum test in both wet and dry areas.</p>
<p>Our installation services in <span data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Belmont&quot;}" data-sheets-userformat="{&quot;2&quot;:513,&quot;3&quot;:{&quot;1&quot;:0},&quot;12&quot;:0}">Belmont </span>can tailor the type of flooring we use to your needs, so feel free to get in touch via our website if you want something specific. Slip-resistance can be found in a lot of different flooring types, so you should make sure you get one that you want.</p>
<h2>Greenhouses and Indoor Farms</h2>
<p>Comfort flooring can be useful as resin floors for indoor or vertical farming, offering more heat control, flexibility, and a UV stable floor finish. Comfort floor can also be made in any colour, so these floors are often selected to manipulate lighting requirements. This is why Comfort Floors have been so widely selected for legally approved UK cannabis farms.</p>
<p>If you want a certain kind of comfort flooring for your farm or greenhouse, let us know, and we can put something together. The more specific you are, the easier it becomes to provide comfort flooring that works.</p>
<h2>Decorative Resin Flooring for Living and Dining Areas</h2>
<p>There are many options for residential floor finishes such as UV-stable comfort flooring, self-levelling resin floor, FeRFA-approved ESD flooring, liquid lino, vinyl, or even plain white reflective flooring. Comfort floors are the perfect option for these areas, they allow you to be creative with design, stand the test of time, and offer a modern, seamless finish which creates the illusion of space in your home.</p>
<p>Our service in <span data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Belmont&quot;}" data-sheets-userformat="{&quot;2&quot;:513,&quot;3&quot;:{&quot;1&quot;:0},&quot;12&quot;:0}">Belmont </span>offers a range of floor finishes for living and dining areas, so contact us if you want some great flooring to cap off your home improvement project. Although installing cushioned polyurethane liquid vinyl flooring can sound complicated, it can be a simple project with our assistance.</p>
