<h2>FAQs</h2>
<h3>Are Resin Comfort Floors Expensive?</h3>
<p>Resin flooring can often be more expensive in the short term than using other materials, this can be as a result of a potential increase in cost of materials as well as the outlay for specialists trained resin contractors to install the product. Taking into consideration the value you are receiving for your money we would say that resin comfort flooring is a good investment mainly for the fact that it is very durable. The flooring being very durable means that you will not need to pay more money to have the cheaper, less durable flooring replaced.</p>
<h3>What is the life expectancy of resin comfort floors?</h3>
<p>With the right care and maintenance, resin comfort floor can last between 10-20 years. This can be made even longer with the correct routine refurbishment of the topcoat. A handy thing with resin comfort flooring, at the end of their lifespan they can simply be overlaid whereas with sheet vinyl or linoleum this typically needs to be removed or disposed of.</p>
<h3>Is Resin Comfort Flooring chemical resistant?</h3>
<p>Epoxy, polyurethane, MMA and polyurethane concrete all exhibit good resistance to a range of chemicals associated with cleaning agents or foodstuffs. For more aggressive chemicals or food and beverages ingredients such as hydrochloric acid, sugars, oils, blood and detergents, heavy-duty polyurethane concrete provides a resistant surface underfoot.</p>
<h3>How often do Resin Floor coatings require repair and maintenance?</h3>
<p>Resin floorings are seamless in nature and don&#8217;t include joins or grout lines, which are susceptible to harbouring dirt, grease, bacteria and stains in general. General dirt and dust can be easily swept, mopped or hoovered away according to manufacturer&#8217;s guidelines based on the profile of the floor.</p>
<p>Resin flooring is very durable and strong, meaning the flooring will have an extended service life compared to other floor coverings. Installed property and with the correct maintenance can last for many years without cracking or peeling, as a customer this is great because you wont need to carry out repairs or replace the floor as frequently if you use less durable materials.</p>
